cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD 

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and the challenges of dealing with non-standard or non-canonical language. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the need for proper algorithms to handle this type of data, which suggests that it could also fit into the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper touches on the social and demographic dimensions of language, which could make it relevant to the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing).
